results.name: G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0
results.description:
Disclaimer: Please be aware of paint fragility regarding the first layer of color on the upper. Due to the thin coating of paint, colors may rub off.

Introducing the Nike Air Force 1 Low G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0, the third installment in the highly coveted collaboration between Nike and South Korean artist G-Dragon utilizing the Air Force 1 base. This special edition features a black leather upper that wears away over time to reveal hidden artwork by G-Dragon, adding a personal, creative touch to every pair. The sneaker showcases contrasting swooshes in yellow, pink, and blue, with a signature sunflower logo on the tongue and custom graphics on the insoles, giving this sneaker a vibrant and artistic vibe.

In keeping with the Air Force 1’s legendary status in both basketball and streetwear, the Para-Noise 3.0 incorporates G-Dragon’s unique artistic flair with features like brushstrokes along the midsole, custom pins, and a special-edition box. Since its debut in 1982, the Air Force 1 has evolved into one of the most iconic sneakers in Nike’s lineup, and this collaboration adds yet another layer of creativity to its storied history.

Released on September 14, 2024, the Nike Air Force 1 Low G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0 retailed at $200. The black, new emerald, pinkfire, tour yellow, and blue gale colorway, paired with G-Dragon’s signature artwork, makes this release a statement piece for both sneakerheads and art enthusiasts alike. This collaboration continues to redefine what a sneaker can be—a canvas for both fashion and expression.

results.name: Flax Wheat
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax Wheat
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax Wheat pays unofficial homage to the classic wheat Timberland work boot with its monochromatic flax suede uppers and overlays. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax Wheat originally released in September of 2019 for $100, restocked in April of 2022 for $130 and currently sits at a retail price of $135.

results.name: Supreme Baroque Brown
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme Baroque Brown
results.description:
The Supreme Air Force 1 is back, this time in a classic brown colorway fit for your fall rotation. results.name: Off-White Varsity Maize
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid SP Off-White Varsity Maize
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid SP Off White Varsity Maize represents a collaboration between Nike and Virgil Abloh’s fashion house Off-White. This sneaker takes an iconic silhouette and a retro colorway and infuses it with hallmark Off-White creativity.​
​​
​The Off White X Nike Air Force 1 Mid-Top Varsity Maize SP sports an upper with a base of tumbled white leather and perforations in the toe box. The overlays and ankle strap are maize-colored tumbled leather, while the side-panel Nike swoosh is white tumbled leather. The laces are maize and an extra pair of white laces threads through fly cables on the upper. The white foam midsole houses visible Air and sits atop a maize rubber outsole where the classic AF1 traction pattern has been enhanced with track spikes.​
​​
​What we love most about this creative shoe is the Off-White branding. Characteristic Off-White text appears on the medial upper while a white grim reaper graphic is embroidered on the lateral heel. The Nike Air Force 1 Mid SP Off White Varsity Maze was released on November 9, 2023, for a retail price of $205.

results.name: Drake NOCTA Certified Lover Boy
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Drake NOCTA Certified Lover Boy
results.description:
Previously dubbed "Certified Lover Boy", the new premium Drake-inspired AF1 is now known as the "Love You Forever." This sentiment is inspired by Drake’s favorite childhood book with subtle added details of the scripted "Love You Forever" on the midsole, in the same white color. results.name: White Swoosh Panda
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White Swoosh Panda
results.description: The Nike Air Force 1 07 Low White Swoosh Panda is a stylish and versatile sneaker that combines classic design with modern features. The shoe features a white leather upper with black accents and a panda graphic on the heel. The iconic Nike Swoosh is also featured in white on the sides. The shoe is made with high-quality materials, including a durable rubber sole and a comfortable foam midsole. The release date for this shoe is January 31, 2023, and with a retail price of $130. Whether you're looking for a casual everyday shoe or a stylish addition to your sneaker collection, the Nike Air Force 1 07 Low White Swoosh Panda is a great choice.

results.name: Linen (2016/2024)
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen (2016/2024)
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen is a special edition sneaker that was released exclusively for the Japan market back in 2001 and then re-released in 2016 to celebrate the opening of Kith's Miami store. They were re-released on a wider scale in 2024.

The shoe features a light brown (linen) colorway with atmosphere pink and true white accents. Atmosphere pink is seen on the Swoosh and outsole while true white appears on the laces and midsole. The shoe maintains the Air Force 1 signature design with the stitching around the midsole and placement of panels on the upper and sides.

What we love about the Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen (2016/2024) is the thick sole unit which incorporates Air units to deliver responsive cushioning across the whole underfoot. This helps to improve comfort especially when wearing the shoes for an extended period. The shoes were released for a retail price of $120 on December 1st, 2016. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen (2016/2024) was re-released for a retail price of $135 on June 13th, 2024.

results.name: Fresh White
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Fresh White
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Fresh is composed of an all-white leather construction with vamp perforations, Swoosh overlays, and a thick Air sole in a signature style. Instead of traditionally embroidered detailing at the tongue and heel, this model adds its own twist with subtle, debossed detailing for an elevated look.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Fresh released in July of 2022 and retailed for $140.

results.name: Black White (2023)
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black White (2023)
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black White (2023) gives the AF 1 Low a stealthy makeover with a black base and branding details in white.

At the Black White (2023) Nike Air Force 1 Low '07, The leather upper, midsole, outsole, laces, and lining come in black, while the branding on the tongue and the heel tab features white. The leather heel tab showcases ‘NIKE AIR’ and a Swoosh, while the tongue displays ‘NIKE AIR FORCE 1’ and the insole reveals ‘NIKE.’ In addition, the classic leather Swoosh also comes in bright white. Perforations on the toebox and the side panels allow the foot to breathe, while the laces provide a secure front closure.

Our experts at StockX like the encapsulated Air unit in the heel because it’s a heritage design element and provides responsive cushioning. The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black White (2023) was released on September 18, 2023, and sold for $110.

results.name: Suede Cacao Wow (Women's)
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Suede Cacao Wow (Women's)
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Suede Cacao Wow (Women’s) lives up to its name, immersing itself in rich brown hues that envelop the entire exclusive women's shoe.

Crafted from supple suede, the Suede Cacao Wow Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 (Women's) boasts a luxurious texture. Adorned in a sumptuous Cacao Wow color scheme, every detail, from the laces to the Swoosh to the outsole, is bathed in this rich monochromatic palette. The uniformity of this design is subtly interrupted by touches of Sand Drift on the tag, stitching, liner, and speckled midsole. Brand recognition is solidified with the addition of the signature Swoosh logo on the sides, and the design is elegantly completed with a durable brown AF1 rubber sole.

The defining feature of the Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Suede Cacao Wow (Women’s) lies in its tonal design. The harmonious blend of the Cacao Wow colorway, coupled with understated pops of Sand Drift, creates a subdued yet stylish statement. The sneaker debuted for $120 on October 17th, 2023.

Unveiled on July 28, 2023, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition is more than just a sneaker; it's the embodiment of Travis’ creative genius, this shoe echoes with the sounds and themes of his groundbreaking album, 'Utopia’.

But there's more. The Utopia graphic doesn't just serve aesthetic vibes; it’s a celebration of music and streetwear colliding. The fusion of leather and subtle design details crafts an aesthetic that's both sleek and statement-making. Dive into the Utopia with this pair of sneakers that retailed at $150.

results.name: Off-White Black
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Black
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White honors the 40th Anniversary of the Nike Air Force 1 by refreshing the classic design with Abloh's signature avante-garde style. It arrives with a black, wood grain-textured lightweight mesh upper with ripstop collar straps and clear TPU Swooshes. From there, a warped midsole with multi-colored sections of a track-inspired spiked outsole reference past Nike Off-White designs like the Nike Waffle Racer and Air Zoom Tempo Next%.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Black released in June of 2022 and retailed for $185.

results.name: Terror Squad Blackout
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low QS Terror Squad Blackout
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low QS in Terror Squad Blackout comes in a sleek black and white colorway. It also features references to the Terror Squad, the hip-hop group formed in the late 1990s with Fat Joe as a lead member.
​
​This sneaker features a white leather base with prominent black leather overlays on the heel, lining the perforated toebox, and around the laces – providing the Nike Air Force 1 Low QS with striking contrast. The cushioned midsole allows for prolonged wear. Terror Squad branding is evident in the white embroidered "TS" and "JC" initials at the heel, with "JC" being a reference to Fat Joe’s other nickname, Joey Clark. A Swoosh in black crosses the midsole.
​
​At StockX, we think this shoe stands out because of the bold contrast of the black and white leather throughout the shoe. The black overlays on the white leather give this shoe a classic, yet eye-catching look, making it appropriate for wear with any outfit. The Nike Air Force 1 Low QS Terror Squad Blackout was released on September 16th, 2023, for a retail price of $150.

results.name: Off-White Pine Green
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green
results.description:
Off-White and Nike are partnering together again on another Air Force 1 sneaker collaboration, with the release of the Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green.

Nike’s Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green is constructed using green premium leather throughout the body of the sneaker. Nike used white accents, the sneakers branding, zip tie, Swooshes, and midsole. The sneakers draw inspiration from Track and Field shoes with a spike like design on the outsoles.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green released April 28, 2023, with a retail price of $205.

results.name: Halloween Skull
results.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Halloween Skull
results.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Halloween Skull brings a haunting new twist to one of Nike’s most iconic models. Featuring a cracked red & black leather upper, this Halloween-inspired sneaker is both spooky and stylish. The skull theme continues with an embossed black skull on the toe box, while the custom insole showcases a series of skull graphics to enhance the Halloween vibe. This is one of the most unique Air Force 1 designs in recent memory.

The Halloween Skull edition of the Air Force 1 Low Retro retains the timeless shape and comfort the model is known for, but adds a seasonal twist with the eerie cracked leather and crimson accents. The deep red underlay beneath the black cracked leather adds a sinister touch, making this pair perfect for Halloween or any time you want to stand out with a bold look.

Released on October 24, 2024, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Halloween Skull retailed for $130. With its sleek color scheme and spooky design, this limited-edition sneaker is a must-have for both Air Force 1 fans and those looking to make a statement this Halloween season.
